      {
        "id": 2433836,
        "name": "Luis Manuel Debuque Monreal Ermita\u00f1o",
        "username": "LMD_Ermitano",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/lmd_ermitano/{size}/77101_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-06-18T06:53:41.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>From the wine list of Campagne (1* Michelin) in Kilkenny, Ireland, dinner of Friday the 25th May 2018. I was with my wife, eldest son, niece &amp; her husband; so I ordered 2 bottles (at \u201conly\u201d 120\u20ac/bottle restaurant price, it was a bargain).</p>\n<p>Relatively light, cool, steely/flinty, lemony, slight saline and sea shell touches to its dominant apple. Good freshness and lively acidity. Light-footed and cool. Didn\u2019t notice it putting on significant weight in glass. Not as much depth of fruit as I know Raveneau\u2019s wine to have; but that\u2019s not necessarily a bad thing for me - just noticed it. It brought Louis Michel\u2019s and Laurent Tribut\u2019s style to mind.</p>\n<p>Too bad there were no fresh oysters available that night. Would have been wonderful with this wine.<br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/9/e/9e92e8e67b8573589b0b221feed8854317972dca.jpeg\" alt=\"A23BD732-7D6F-413A-8CF6-99AF294CE246.jpeg\" data-base62-sha1=\"mCObY6nHwWr61WWznKXJkteQ2aS\" width=\"360\" height=\"480\"></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 10,
