      {
        "id": 2433856,
        "name": "Joshua Kates",
        "username": "Joshua_Kates",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/e47774/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-06-18T11:10:31.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks, Noel,<br>\nGood to see you posting here again. (I found some Raveneau still cheaper last year in France.) Do you think the vintage accounted for the lack of \u201cdepth of fruit,\u201d as I agree these often tend to drink simply more like great Burgundy than Chablis?</p>",
