      {
        "id": 2433859,
        "name": "Luis Manuel Debuque Monreal Ermita\u00f1o",
        "username": "LMD_Ermitano",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/lmd_ermitano/{size}/77101_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-06-18T11:28:52.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>From what little I know of 2012 Chablis, it\u2019s likely to be  the weather (as Montmains is left of the river) and/or picking was a bit early. Could also be that younger vines were involved. Who really knows (except the winemaker)?</p>\n<p>Best,</p>\n<p>N</p>",
        "post_number": 3,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 10,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T04:53:28.232Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
