        "created_at": "2018-06-19T08:18:57.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"LMD Ermita\u00f1o\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n LMD Ermita\u00f1o:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I should have mentioned that I was referring to Tribut\u2019s village Chablis, which is what I usually have when having simply prepared seafood (fresh oysters, steamed crab, etc.). Minimal/old oak, no b\u00e2ttonage, etc. His Beauroy and C\u00f4te de L\u00e9chet (the only other two of his lines imported in Manila) are quite different.</p>\n<p>I, myself, suspected the '12 Raveneau Monts Mains was too young; but, well, it was the one I saw on the restaurant\u2019s wine list that I wanted. Even at a 1* Michelin, in Kilkenny, Ireland, fine wine lists are not the best. One works with what one is presented at the time.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Absolutely!</p>",
